---
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for AstroSEO.io." pathname="/privacy/">
  <section class="hero policy-hero">
    <p class="meta">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: {siteConfig.lastPolicyUpdate}</p>
  </section>

  <article class="policy-card prose">
    <h2>Static hosting and server logs</h2>
    <p>
      AstroSEO.io is a static website hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may
      process connection, security, and server-log information such as IP
      addresses, request paths, user agents, timestamps, and threat signals to
      deliver and protect the site. That processing is governed by Cloudflare's
      own policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Search and measurement tools</h2>
    <p>
      Google Search Console is used to monitor crawling, indexing, and search
      performance. The current site source does not install a visitor analytics
      script, advertising script, account system, contact form, or newsletter
      form. If analytics or advertising is introduced later, this policy and
      any required consent mechanism will be updated before deployment.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      Articles link to GitHub, hosting providers, documentation, and other
      third-party services. Following an external link subjects the visitor to
      that service's privacy practices, which AstroSEO.io does not control.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy-related corrections can be raised through the public
      <a href={siteConfig.issuesUrl}>GitHub Issues page</a>. Do not include
      personal or sensitive information in a public issue.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
